frameDefinitions: A Cause leads to the formation of a Created_entity.
A Cause, animate or inanimate, causes a process, the Effect, to begin.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
An Agent acts to begin the life of a Process.
An Developer develops a Product, in some cases for a Company.    '' 'The development of a profitable product will be necessary for the company to stay afloat.
frameExamples: The murder of Sergei Kirov <t>set off</t> a chain of events that culminated in the Great Terror of the 1930s.
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
After discovering her knack for organization, she decided to try to  <t>launch</t> a career in human resources.
The <t>development</t> of a profitable product will be necessary for the company to stay afloat. INI
